content.description: An unlikely climb for the Forks, Orange Cake is face climbing over small, tricky gear placements. Gray and orange basalt spattered with yellow and brown lichen. A low angle slab is followed by an unprotected section of cobble climbing, then sequential beta to the summit.
content.protection: Small to tiny cams and nuts.
content.location: Also viewed from the Prow, Orange Cake is easily scoped from the top of Fluke or Flounder, and accessed easiest by rappelling the Column itself.

content.description: West Facing, this wall receives a day full of sun, with shady mornings. Protruding horns are great for setting up anchors or a top-rope.
